=== Diseases ===

Wickerbeast lore includes species-specific conditions:

* '''Berserker's Disease''' — Develops from prolonged malnutrition in famine conditions, exacerbating the species' naturally headstrong temperament into constant aggression, poor cognitive function, mania, and insomnia.
* '''Sphinx Syndrome''' — A hereditary condition in which a Wickerbeast is born hairless and deaf. Affected individuals may have horns, but these tend to be small or fragile. Kingbeasts with Sphinx Syndrome face particular social stigma in King-ruled clans, though other Kingbeasts tend to accept them.

== Culture and society ==

=== Religion ===

Wickerbeasts are polytheistic and worship multiple gods. Their primary deity is '''Idris''', the god of the sun and light. It is not uncommon for a Wickerbeast to devote themselves entirely to a single god.

