== History ==

The Wickerbeast species was first conceptualized by Daemon_Lady (Simone White) in 2013, beginning with a preliminary sketch. Two additional designs were developed in late 2014. The first official community group was a Facebook page established in early 2014, with an inaugural moderation team comprising Guts, Rune (PineWarden), Hamada, Mavi, and Tombo (Wolpertingerwhite).

The original four subtypes—Standard, King, Swamp, and Rogue—were introduced during this early period. Between 2019 and 2022, three additional subtypes were added: Aerions (created by Daemon_Lady) and Dwellers and Pelagics (created by PineWarden).

On January 5, 2022, ownership and rights for the species were officially transferred to PineWarden. All subsequent development and administrative oversight has been managed by PineWarden and the current administration team. The species is considered a collaborative effort between Daemon_Lady's foundational concepts and PineWarden's developments. The original Facebook group was archived in August 2025. The species lore, design guidelines, and community resources are now maintained through the Wicker Cave website.

== Avatar bases ==

Being an open species, multiple independent creators have produced VRChat-ready models based on the Wickerbeast design. These avatars are not created by the species owners but by third-party artists.

=== Wickerbeast by Zab ===

The Wickerbeast avatar by '''Zab''' (also known as lixyco or VR_Zab) is a VRChat and VTuber-ready model first made available on Patreon in June 2020 and later on Gumroad. Zab specializes in from-scratch VR avatars and distributes models across multiple platforms.

=== Wickerbeast King by Jin A ===

The '''Wickerbeast King''' avatar by Jin A is a VRChat-ready model based on the King subtype, available on Gumroad. It features:

* PhysBones with dynamics on hair, tail, and tongue
* Poiyomi Toon shader
* 4K textures with multiple color presets
* A female variant with optional chest dynamics
* VRM conversion package for use with applications such as VSeeFace

A community-made Quest-optimized version is also available. The model has received over 900 ratings on Gumroad.

== Assets ==

A third-party accessory ecosystem has developed around the Wickerbeast avatars, with creators offering compatible add-ons across platforms such as Gumroad, and Jinxxy. Including:
* Clothing items (hoodies, sweaters, pants, swimsuits)
* Alternative textures and color packs
* Hair and horn variations
* Face tracking add-ons
* Body modification options
* Jewelry and accessories

